# 🧮 Java Swing Calculator

A simple and fully functional desktop calculator application built using **Java Swing**.  
The calculator provides a modern iOS-inspired dark UI with basic arithmetic operations and interactive buttons.

---

## 📌 Project Overview

This project demonstrates GUI development using Java Swing, event handling, and basic object-oriented programming concepts.

The application allows users to perform mathematical calculations through a graphical user interface.

---

## ✨ Features

✅ Addition (+)  
✅ Subtraction (-)  
✅ Multiplication (×)  
✅ Division (÷)  
✅ Percentage (%) calculation  
✅ Positive/Negative toggle (+/-)  
✅ Clear calculator (AC)  
✅ Decimal number support  
✅ Automatic removal of unnecessary `.0` values  
✅ Dark theme UI  
✅ Responsive button interactions  

---

## 🖥️ Preview

The calculator contains:

| Button Type | Purpose |
|------------|---------|
| ⚫ Dark Gray | Numbers (0-9) and decimal |
| 🟠 Orange | Mathematical operators |
| ⚪ Light Gray | Utility functions |

---

## 🛠 Technologies Used

- Java
- Java Swing
- AWT
- Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)

---

## 📋 Requirements

Before running this project, install:

- Java Development Kit (JDK) 8 or above

Check Java installation:

```bash
java -version
````

---

## 📂 Project Structure

```
Java-Swing-Calculator/
│
├── src/
│   │
│   ├── Calculator.java
│   └── Main.java
│
└── README.md
```

---

## 🚀 How to Run

### 1. Clone Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/Kv23-corder/JavaCalculator.git
```

Move into the project:

```bash
cd JavaCalculator
```

---

### 2. Compile the Project

```bash
javac src/Calculator.java src/Main.java -d out
```

---

### 3. Run Application

```bash
java -cp out Main
```

---

## 🧠 Application Logic

The calculator follows a simple:

```
First Number → Operator → Second Number → Result
```

Example:

```
10 + 5 = 15
```

### Variables Used

| Variable | Description               |
| -------- | ------------------------- |
| num1     | Stores first number       |
| operator | Stores selected operation |
| num2     | Stores second number      |
| result   | Stores calculation output |

---

## ➕ Supported Operations

| Operation      | Example    |
| -------------- | ---------- |
| Addition       | 5 + 3 = 8  |
| Subtraction    | 9 - 4 = 5  |
| Multiplication | 6 × 2 = 12 |
| Division       | 8 ÷ 2 = 4  |
| Percentage     | 50% = 0.5  |
| Sign Change    | 5 → -5     |

